  "prompt": "What is the best movie that didn't win an Oscar?",
  "response": "While opinions on the \"best\" movie can be subjective, several acclaimed films did not win an Oscar despite their significant impact and popularity. Some notable examples include:\n\n1. **\"The Shawshank Redemption\" (1994)** \u2013 Widely regarded as one of the greatest films of all time, it was nominated for seven Academy Awards but did not win any.\n2. **\"Vertigo\" (1958)** \u2013 Alfred Hitchcock's masterpiece often ranks high on lists of the greatest films ever made but did not win any Oscars.\n3. **\"Citizen Kane\" (1941)** \u2013 Frequently cited as the greatest film ever, it won one Oscar for Best Original Screenplay but did not win Best Picture.\n4. **\"Pulp Fiction\" (1994)** \u2013 Quentin Tarantino's groundbreaking film won Best Original Screenplay but missed out on Best Picture.\n5. **\"2001: A Space Odyssey\" (1968)** \u2013 Stanley Kubrick's influential science fiction film won an Oscar for Best Visual Effects but was not honored in major categories.\n\nUltimately, the \"best\" movie that didn't win an Oscar can vary based on personal taste and criteria, but these films are often highlighted in discussions about Oscar snubs.",
